meanings.definition: Text or images produced on paper or another material using a printing press or similar method.
meanings.sent1: The printed document contained important information about the event.
meanings.sent2: I picked up the printed flyer from the front desk.
meanings.sent3: The printed menu made me hungry just by looking at it.
meanings.sent4: Her dress was a colorful canvas of printed flowers.
meanings.sent5: The library was filled with rows of printed books waiting to be read.

meanings.definition: Having words or images in ink on paper or another material.
meanings.sent1: The printed page was filled with beautiful illustrations.
meanings.sent2: She showed me the printed invitation to the party.
meanings.sent3: The printed map helped us find our way through the city.
meanings.sent4: His shirt had a unique printed design that caught everyone's eye.
meanings.sent5: The printed poster was hung on the wall for everyone to see.

meanings.definition: To produce books, newspapers, etc., by a process involving the transfer of text or images to paper or another material.
meanings.sent1: The company printed thousands of copies of the new book.
meanings.sent2: We printed the latest edition of the newspaper this morning.
meanings.sent3: He printed out the directions to the meeting so he wouldn't get lost.
meanings.sent4: The artist printed her own illustrations to sell at the market.
meanings.sent5: The machine printed the labels for the products efficiently.
